title: supernatural

description.plain:
Hypothesized to be written at the time Ariana first met Slater, track 6, “supernatural”, suits itself with a low-tempo R&B beat, offering several occasions of reverb to both build upon the celestial imagery in this track; as well as to further emphasize her irresistible nature over Slater.

“Supernatural”, in its simplest terminology from Merriam-Webster, means:

of or relating to an order of existence beyond the visible observable universe

In relation to both the nature of the film this album is based on, Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind, as well as Ariana’s own personal affairs, this term directly correlates, in emotion, to how Ariana feels ‘inseparable’; she’s feeling it take over her entire state of mind and she doesn’t mind at all.

She constructs this sense through extended metaphors and semantics of togetherness, like when she states the situation is akin ‘like the moon needs the stars’ – the celestial nature suggested here may also serve as an allusion towards sexual intercourse and lustful desires, as seen stated prior to this lyric:

Need your hands all up on my body

The point of sexual allusions within this track is accepted by Ariana Grande for Amazon Music.

An interesting tidbit to notice is that Ariana is also heavily superstitious, believing in the aforementioned “supernatural”; therefore, it is fitting how Ariana suggests that it is some exterior power pulling them together, not fighting it as it’s part of the beings will.
